It is up to the Interior ministry to appoint an appropriate authority to investigate the two accidents involving police choppers, the Kenya Civil Aviation Authority said yesterday. The authority said it is investigating crashes involving two civil aircrafts . Investigations of accidents involving state aircraft, as defined in the Civil Aviation Act, is conducted by the appropriate state authority. In this case, the ministry responsible for the National Police Service shall determine the appropriate authority to investigate the two accidents indicated on the list above, KCAA corporate communications manager Salim Bakari said.He said accidents involving civil aircrafts are being investigated by the Air Accident Investigation Department of the Transport ministry. A police chopper crashed at Mathare North on Thursday and another crashed at Wilson on August 22.